# Basket Service

## Architecture

- Follow Clean Architecture: `Basket.API` → `Basket.Application` → `Basket.Core` ← `Basket.Infrastructure`.
- Use CQRS via `Common.Mediator` — add commands/queries in `Basket.Application`, handlers in `Handlers/`, register assemblies in `Program.cs` via `AddMediator`.
- Use Mapperly `BasketMapper.Instance` for entity/response/event mapping; do not add AutoMapper or register the mapper in DI.
- Keep HTTP controllers thin — delegate to mediator; checkout publish logic stays in controllers (`IPublishEndpoint`) as existing pattern.

## Data & persistence

- Baskets live in Redis via `IDistributedCache`; repository is `Basket.Infrastructure/Repositories/BasketRepository.cs`.
- Cache key is the basket `UserName` string — no key prefix or schema versioning.
- JSON deserialization uses case-insensitive property names — preserve this when changing serializer options.
- Register `IBasketRepository` → `BasketRepository` in `Program.cs`; Redis connection from `CacheSettings:ConnectionString`.

## Messaging & contracts

- Checkout publishes integration events then deletes the basket — v1 uses `BasketCheckoutEvent`, v2 uses `BasketCheckoutEventV2` (different namespaces and Ordering consumers).
- MassTransit is publish-only here — no receive endpoints in `Program.cs`.
- Queue names for downstream consumers are in `Infrastructure/EventBus.Messages/Common/EventBusConstant.cs` — do not hardcode queue strings in Basket.
- Ocelot routes upstream `/Basket/*` to `/api/v1/Basket/*` or `/api/v2/Basket/Checkout` — keep gateway paths aligned when renaming actions.

## Discount integration

- Discount lookup runs in `CreateShoppingCartCommandHandler` via `DiscountGrpcService` (gRPC to Discount service).
- Respect `BypassDiscount:Enabled` config flag — when true, skip gRPC calls entirely.
- `DiscountGrpcService` degrades gracefully (zero discount) on gRPC failures — do not throw from discount lookup in the handler path.

## Do not

- Do not add EF Core or SQL persistence for carts — Redis is the sole store for this service.
- Do not add MassTransit consumers in Basket — Ordering owns checkout consumption.
- Do not assume authentication — no auth scheme is configured despite `UseAuthorization()` in the pipeline.
- Do not change checkout event shapes without coordinating with `Services/Ordering` consumers.

